# Review 4: Java NullPointerException & Streams

**Severity:** High  
**Language:** Java

## Original Task Given to AI

> Write a method that takes a list of users, filters out inactive users, and returns their email addresses in uppercase.

## Buggy AI-Generated Code

```java
// ❌ BUGGY CODE
public List<String> getActiveUserEmails(List<User> users) {
    List<String> emails = new ArrayList<>();
    
    for (User user : users) {
        if (user.isActive()) {
            emails.add(user.getEmail().toUpperCase());
        }
    }
    
    return emails;
}

// ✅ CORRECTED CODE
import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

public List<String> getActiveUserEmails(List<User> users) {
    if (users == null) {
        return Collections.emptyList();
    }
    
    return users.stream()
        .filter(Objects::nonNull)
        .filter(User::isActive)
        .map(User::getEmail)
        .filter(Objects::nonNull)
        .map(String::toUpperCase)
        .collect(Collectors.toList());
}

// Even safer with Optional
public List<String> getActiveUserEmailsSafe(List<User> users) {
    return Optional.ofNullable(users)
        .orElse(Collections.emptyList())
        .stream()
        .filter(Objects::nonNull)
        .filter(user -> user.isActive())
        .map(user -> Optional.ofNullable(user.getEmail())
            .map(String::toUpperCase)
            .orElse(null))
        .filter(Objects::nonNull)
        .collect(Collectors.toList());
}
